CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 9, 1960, pg. A2, reads: "Central Baptist Church Plays Host - NAACP Youth Rally Backs Dixie 'Sit-In' War - In the Thick of the Fight - Unlike many other persons in the Western Pennsylvania area, the speakers shown above were among those who indicated that they were in the thick of the fight for equal rights by attending an NAACP youth rally last Friday night at Central Baptist Church. Urging the endorsement of the fight for equal rights in Dixie, not only with words but with money, were left to right: Atty. Derrick Bell, former Pittsburgh NAACP executive secretary, now of the NAACP legal staff in New York... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Atty Derrick Bell speaking during NAACP Youth Rally in Central Baptist Church
